---
// src/components/astro/Faq.astro
---
<section class="w-full bg-canvas-soft py-16 md:py-24 border-t border-ink/5 dark:bg-[#1a1d1a] dark:border-canvas-soft/10" aria-labelledby="faq-title">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-6">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 id="faq-title" class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-wise font-black tracking-tight mb-4 text-ink dark:text-canvas">
        Frequently Asked Questions
      </h2>
      <p class="text-body text-base dark:text-canvas-soft/80">
        Answers to common questions regarding work hours tracking and payroll calculations.
      </p>
    </div>

    {/* Accordion Questions using semantic Details/Summary */}
    <div class="space-y-4">
      
      <details class="group bg-canvas rounded-xl border border-canvas-soft/80 overflow-hidden transition-default [&_summary::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden dark:bg-[#111311] dark:border-canvas-soft/10">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 text-base font-bold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none select-none group-open:border-b group-open:border-canvas-soft dark:text-canvas dark:group-open:border-canvas-soft/10">
          <span>How do I convert hours and minutes to decimal hours?</span>
          <span class="transition-default group-open:rotate-180">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-mute dark:text-canvas-soft/50" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="p-6 text-sm text-body leading-relaxed bg-canvas-soft/10 dark:text-canvas-soft/80">
          <p class="mb-3">
            To convert minutes to decimal hours, divide the minutes by <span class="font-bold">60</span>. For example:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-3 space-y-1">
            <li>15 minutes = 15 / 60 = <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-ink dark:text-canvas">0.25 hours</span></li>
            <li>30 minutes = 30 / 60 = <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-ink dark:text-canvas">0.50 hours</span></li>
            <li>45 minutes = 45 / 60 = <span class="font-mono font-semibold text-ink dark:text-canvas">0.75 hours</span></li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Then, add the result back to your whole hours. If you worked <span class="font-bold">8 hours and 15 minutes</span>, your decimal hours would be <span class="font-mono font-bold text-ink dark:text-canvas">8.25 hours</span>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-canvas rounded-xl border border-canvas-soft/80 overflow-hidden transition-default [&_summary::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden dark:bg-[#111311] dark:border-canvas-soft/10">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 text-base font-bold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none select-none group-open:border-b group-open:border-canvas-soft dark:text-canvas dark:group-open:border-canvas-soft/10">
          <span>How does automatic overnight shift detection work?</span>
          <span class="transition-default group-open:rotate-180">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-mute dark:text-canvas-soft/50" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="p-6 text-sm text-body leading-relaxed bg-canvas-soft/10 dark:text-canvas-soft/80">
          <p>
            When you enter an end time that is chronologically earlier than your start time (for example, starting at <span class="font-mono">10:00 PM</span> and ending at <span class="font-mono">6:00 AM</span>), the calculator automatically assumes a midnight crossover. It adds 24 hours to the end time to compute the elapsed shift duration as <span class="font-bold">8.00 hours</span>, rather than resulting in a negative total.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-canvas rounded-xl border border-canvas-soft/80 overflow-hidden transition-default [&_summary::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden dark:bg-[#111311] dark:border-canvas-soft/10">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 text-base font-bold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none select-none group-open:border-b group-open:border-canvas-soft dark:text-canvas dark:group-open:border-canvas-soft/10">
          <span>Why do employers require decimal hours for payroll?</span>
          <span class="transition-default group-open:rotate-180">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-mute dark:text-canvas-soft/50" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="p-6 text-sm text-body leading-relaxed bg-canvas-soft/10 dark:text-canvas-soft/80">
          <p>
            Decimal hours are much easier to multiply by an hourly rate of pay. If your pay is <span class="font-bold">$20.00/hour</span> and you work <span class="font-bold">7 hours and 45 minutes</span>, multiplying <span class="font-mono">20 * 7:45</span> directly is mathematically incorrect. Instead, you convert 45 minutes to <span class="font-mono">0.75</span>, resulting in <span class="font-mono">7.75 hours</span>. The calculation becomes a simple multiplication: <span class="font-mono">$20.00 * 7.75 = $155.00</span>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-canvas rounded-xl border border-canvas-soft/80 overflow-hidden transition-default [&_summary::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden dark:bg-[#111311] dark:border-canvas-soft/10">
        <summary class="flex justify-between items-center p-6 text-base font-bold text-ink cursor-pointer list-none select-none group-open:border-b group-open:border-canvas-soft dark:text-canvas dark:group-open:border-canvas-soft/10">
          <span>Is my personal or timesheet data secure on this page?</span>
          <span class="transition-default group-open:rotate-180">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-mute dark:text-canvas-soft/50" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <div class="p-6 text-sm text-body leading-relaxed bg-canvas-soft/10 dark:text-canvas-soft/80">
          <p>
            Yes, your data is completely secure. All calculations, including time parsing and weekly sheet aggregations, are executed locally on your client machine using JavaScript. No timesheet information, shift records, or personal entries are sent or stored on our servers.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
